      <T n="text">0xA09B561D<!--Sims must learn each other's Romantic Boundaries by asking! Select another Sim, choose the <b>“Relationship”</b> category then the <b>“Learn More”</b> category, and finally choose the <b>"Ask about Romantic Boundaries"</b> interaction.
Once a Sim agrees to share this, their reply will appear as a text notification. Their Romantic Boundaries will also be recorded in their Sim Profile page.

--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_Relationships_EomanticBoundaries1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6e976342c1e7175c</T>
      <T n="text">0x89ABA272<!--If a Sim is exploring <b>Romantic Boundaries</b>, they may Reconsider if asked by another Sim. Select another Sim, choose the <b>“Relationship”</b> category, then choose the <b>"Change Relationship"</b> subcategory. Find the <b>"Ask To Reconsider Romantic Boundaries"</b> category. In this category there are social interactions that Sims can use to ask another Sim to Reconsider specific Romantic Boundaries.\n\nIf a Sim is <b>not Exploring Romantic Boundaries</b> they cannot be asked to Reconsider.\n\nLearn more about setting up your Sims' Romantic Boundaries in Lessons under <b>Create A Sim > Identity & Personality > Romantic Boundaries</b>--></T>
    </U>
